1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,268
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,270 --> 00:00:05,270
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,272 --> 00:00:07,272
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:09,141
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:13,014 --> 00:00:15,047
<i>Invisible, indestructible</i>

6
00:00:15,049 --> 00:00:17,182
<i>And completely inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:19,184
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:21,720
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,722 --> 00:00:24,156
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,158 --> 00:00:25,758
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,359
When I say, "jump,"

12
00:00:27,361 --> 00:00:29,228
You say,
"how high?"

13
00:00:32,565 --> 00:00:33,632
We have to tell someone.

14
00:00:33,634 --> 00:00:35,634
<i>The day the dome came down,</i>

15
00:00:35,636 --> 00:00:37,369
<i>We both started</i>
<i>having seizures.</i>

16
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:38,437
Junior:
Those dundee guys,

17
00:00:38,439 --> 00:00:40,105
They'll never bother you again.

18
00:00:40,107 --> 00:00:41,407
Clint:
Please.

19
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:44,510
Another dome?

20
00:00:45,646 --> 00:00:46,712
Norrie.

21
00:00:48,314 --> 00:00:50,616
I love you so much, mom.

22
00:00:51,818 --> 00:00:54,086
Just tell me what you want!

23
00:01:24,117 --> 00:01:26,118
What the hell are
you doing here?

24
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,219
Dad,

25
00:01:27,221 --> 00:01:29,088
Put down the gun.

26
00:01:29,090 --> 00:01:32,091
I asked you a question.

27
00:01:32,093 --> 00:01:34,326
What are you doing in my house?

28
00:01:34,328 --> 00:01:36,295
This is my house, too.

29
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:39,331
Not anymore.

30
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:42,468
You told me to stay away
from angie.

31
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:43,735
She's not here.

32
00:01:43,737 --> 00:01:45,571
How would you know that?

33
00:01:45,573 --> 00:01:47,306
You been stalking the poor girl?

34
00:01:47,308 --> 00:01:49,475
You feel like locking her up
for another week?

35
00:01:49,477 --> 00:01:51,677
I just want to make sure
she's safe.

36
00:01:51,679 --> 00:01:55,147
Did you make her safe
by killing clint dundee?

37
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,416
That's right.

38
00:01:58,384 --> 00:02:00,686
I heard you shot that boy.

39
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:03,589
He attacked angie.

40
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:05,891
I have no sympathy for
the dundee brothers,

41
00:02:05,893 --> 00:02:10,329
But that doesn't qualify you to
be their judge and executioner.

42
00:02:10,331 --> 00:02:12,598
Clint dundee got
what he deserved.

43
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,667
Who are you to say
who deserves to be punished?

44
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:17,836
You're not
in your right mind, junior.

45
00:02:17,838 --> 00:02:21,340
You sound just like your
mother did in the end.

46
00:02:21,342 --> 00:02:23,609
Please don't say that.

47
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:29,214
I'll tell you this, though...

48
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,552
...You're no son of mine.

49
00:02:35,522 --> 00:02:37,589
Not anymore.

50
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:43,428
Now, get out.

51
00:02:44,364 --> 00:02:46,431
I said get
out of here.

52
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:59,545
One thing.

53
00:02:59,547 --> 00:03:04,616
Don't you ever talk
about my mother that way again.

54
00:03:04,618 --> 00:03:06,718
Ever.

55
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:32,411
You're pretty good
at that.

56
00:03:33,514 --> 00:03:36,315
Nice military corners.

57
00:03:36,317 --> 00:03:39,418
I'm pretty sure
you're thinking about a bed.

58
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,553
Same shape.

59
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:43,789
Yeah.

60
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:47,526
Any idea when carolyn and
norrie want to bury her?

61
00:03:47,528 --> 00:03:49,962
They haven't come
downstairs yet.

62
00:03:49,964 --> 00:03:52,831
Can't imagine losing a spouse
like that.

63
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,900
Yeah.

64
00:03:57,637 --> 00:03:59,304
It's strange, huh?

65
00:03:59,306 --> 00:04:00,973
What's that?
Alice dies.

66
00:04:00,975 --> 00:04:03,242
Harriet has a baby.

67
00:04:03,244 --> 00:04:05,644
Same house...

68
00:04:05,646 --> 00:04:07,312
Same day.

69
00:04:09,716 --> 00:04:11,717
Circle of life.

70
00:04:19,492 --> 00:04:22,494
Too busy with your new
girlfriend to go shopping, huh?

71
00:04:22,496 --> 00:04:24,630
Norrie's not
my girlfriend.

72
00:04:24,632 --> 00:04:26,999
She's just my girl,
space, friend.

73
00:04:29,036 --> 00:04:31,303
How could I go
shopping anyway?

74
00:04:31,305 --> 00:04:33,005
Stores have all been looted.

75
00:04:33,007 --> 00:04:34,873
Everyone's running low on food.

76
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:36,875
You could've
taken something, too.

77
00:04:36,877 --> 00:04:38,877
That's stealing.

78
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,946
You've never stolen anything?

79
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:43,015
No. Have you?

80
00:04:43,017 --> 00:04:45,417
Of course I have, dummy.

81
00:04:45,419 --> 00:04:49,021
Duke caught me stealing lipstick
at dee's pharmacy once.

82
00:04:49,023 --> 00:04:51,690
That's why I started
candy striping.

83
00:04:51,692 --> 00:04:53,325
Community service.

84
00:04:53,327 --> 00:04:55,360
Where were you all week, angie?

85
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:56,528
I looked all
over for you.

86
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:57,596
The only person

87
00:04:57,598 --> 00:05:00,332
Who said he saw you was junior.

88
00:05:04,504 --> 00:05:07,306
Well, are you that surprised
that I disappeared?

89
00:05:07,308 --> 00:05:09,308
I'm the screwup, right?

90
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:11,810
I never thought
you were a screwup.

91
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,046
Let's go down to the diner.

92
00:05:14,048 --> 00:05:15,580
We can get something
to eat there.

93
00:05:20,386 --> 00:05:21,720
Hey.

94
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:27,859
How are you feeling?

95
00:05:27,861 --> 00:05:31,930
Well, my mom just died
12 hours ago, so...

96
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:34,099
How do you think?

97
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:36,501
I'm sorry.

98
00:05:37,637 --> 00:05:40,072
We're going to the diner
to get something to eat.

99
00:05:40,074 --> 00:05:41,573
Do you...
I'm not hungry.

100
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:42,741
But don't you think

101
00:05:42,743 --> 00:05:44,009
You should...
Joe.

102
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:47,512
I don't need you
to take care of me.

103
00:05:52,552 --> 00:05:54,953
mmm, thank you, thank you.

104
00:05:54,955 --> 00:05:56,755
Angie:
You're welcome.

105
00:06:00,626 --> 00:06:02,427
This is the last
place in town

106
00:06:02,429 --> 00:06:04,429
With any coffee left.

107
00:06:04,431 --> 00:06:05,831
Enjoy it
while you can.

108
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,799
'cause I don't think
this is the right climate

109
00:06:07,801 --> 00:06:11,436
To be growing
coffee beans.

110
00:06:11,438 --> 00:06:13,505
I see you let
yourself in.

111
00:06:13,507 --> 00:06:16,975
You know who else
let himself in last night?

112
00:06:16,977 --> 00:06:18,543
Your insane son.

113
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,579
Come here.

114
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:23,115
Saying something about clint
and waylon dundee,

115
00:06:23,117 --> 00:06:24,716
How they'd never hurt me again.

116
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,852
Like... Like a wildcat
bringing me a dead mouse

117
00:06:26,854 --> 00:06:28,086
As some kind
of sick offering.

118
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:29,388
It freaked me out.

119
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,589
Angie...
No, you promised me

120
00:06:30,591 --> 00:06:32,124
That you'd protect me.

121
00:06:32,126 --> 00:06:33,992
I told you
that I wouldn't tell anyone

122
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:35,494
About what junior did to me,

123
00:06:35,496 --> 00:06:37,496
And you said
that you would keep him away.

124
00:06:37,498 --> 00:06:39,498
It won't happen again.

125
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,166
I give you my word.

126
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:44,936
Now,

127
00:06:44,938 --> 00:06:46,972
What can I do
to make it up to you?

128
00:06:49,809 --> 00:06:51,943
Well, the diner needs food.

129
00:06:51,945 --> 00:06:54,746
I mean, there's a little,
but it'll go fast.

130
00:06:55,882 --> 00:06:59,184
I think it'll be good
to open this place up again.

131
00:06:59,186 --> 00:07:02,421
Rose would've wanted that.

132
00:07:03,156 --> 00:07:05,624
I'll talk to ollie densmore.

133
00:07:05,626 --> 00:07:08,960
We'll come to an arrangement.

134
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:10,595
You know,
the day's coming when, uh...

135
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:12,664
The only way any of us
are gonna get food

136
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:14,166
Is by taking it out
of the ground.

137
00:07:14,168 --> 00:07:16,735
So, from here

138
00:07:16,737 --> 00:07:19,004
On out...

139
00:07:19,006 --> 00:07:21,072
Got to be smart.

140
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:24,509
"from here on out"?

141
00:07:25,878 --> 00:07:28,547
You think the dome
is gonna be here forever?

142
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:33,685
Big jim:
Julia.

143
00:07:33,687 --> 00:07:35,754
Councilman.

144
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:39,090
How are you doing?

145
00:07:46,532 --> 00:07:48,233
What is that?

146
00:07:48,235 --> 00:07:50,202
It's nothing.

147
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:28,640
Ollie.

148
00:08:35,781 --> 00:08:37,182
Ollie:
I don't expect
you came out here

149
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:40,886
To apologize for casting
aspersions on my good name.

150
00:08:40,888 --> 00:08:43,021
Look, ollie...

151
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:46,958
Chester's mill is coming up
on a serious food shortage.

152
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,728
Now, you and I,
we can...

153
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:52,130
Work together
to solve this situation.

154
00:08:52,132 --> 00:08:54,132
Share our resources.

155
00:08:54,134 --> 00:08:57,636
Well, I know you need my water
to grow crops, but, uh...

156
00:08:57,638 --> 00:08:59,704
What is it you have that I need?

157
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:02,140
Propane.

158
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:04,976
Propane. Ah.

159
00:09:04,978 --> 00:09:08,113
Well, it's helpful,
I'll give you that.

160
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:11,917
My ancestors made do
without irrigation systems

161
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:14,052
Or dvd players.

162
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:16,788
I expect we can get by
without 'em now.

163
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:19,190
So you would starve people

164
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:21,860
Just to get
back at me?

165
00:09:21,862 --> 00:09:23,728
Course not.

166
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,997
But I sure wouldn't mind
starving you out.

167
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:28,867
When this town realizes
that having you as a councilman

168
00:09:28,869 --> 00:09:31,603
Makes for empty stomachs,

169
00:09:31,605 --> 00:09:33,872
They're gonna drum you out
faster than a knife fight

170
00:09:33,874 --> 00:09:35,006
In a phone booth.

171
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:37,008
And I'll be more

172
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:39,277
Than happy to fill your shoes.

173
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:44,215
Best of luck to you, jim.

174
00:09:48,854 --> 00:09:50,855
Glad you came in.

175
00:09:50,857 --> 00:09:53,224
Feel like faking it
as a deputy a while longer?

176
00:09:53,226 --> 00:09:56,094
I told you I'd be happy
to stay on and help in a...

177
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:57,929
Freelance capacity.

178
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:14,846
Junior, what are you doing
in here?

179
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:17,048
I need a gun for patrol.

180
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:20,285
Well, maybe it's better
you left it here.

181
00:10:21,253 --> 00:10:23,788
So, what,
you don't trust me?

182
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:27,926
After what happened yesterday,
I got to say that I don't.

183
00:10:27,928 --> 00:10:29,861
If we weren't so shorthanded
by the dome,

184
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:31,630
I would've fired your ass.

185
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:33,298
So am I on the force or not?

186
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:37,268
Let's call it
probation.

187
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,804
And no gun until I say
you've earned it.

188
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:41,973
Big jim:
Linda.

189
00:10:42,942 --> 00:10:46,011
Linda, I need you.

190
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,882
And you, too, barbie.

191
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:57,789
Ollie densmore's dead set on
keeping that well to himself.

192
00:10:57,791 --> 00:10:59,190
If he thinks
he can toy

193
00:10:59,192 --> 00:11:01,860
With this town
just to satisfy his own...

194
00:11:01,862 --> 00:11:04,095
Power-hungry whims,
he's sorely mistaken.

195
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:06,131
Can't we negotiate with him?

196
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:08,133
I have a better plan.

197
00:11:08,135 --> 00:11:10,268
Eminent domain.

198
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:12,737
It's in the town bylaws.
The right of the government

199
00:11:12,739 --> 00:11:13,972
To confiscate
private property...

200
00:11:13,974 --> 00:11:15,373
Yeah, I know what it is.

201
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:17,242
How do you think
ollie's gonna feel about you

202
00:11:17,244 --> 00:11:19,144
Just marching in there
and taking his land?

203
00:11:19,146 --> 00:11:20,912
That's why I'm bringing
the police.

204
00:11:20,914 --> 00:11:22,280
Get carter.

205
00:11:22,282 --> 00:11:23,882
Junior, too.

206
00:11:23,884 --> 00:11:26,718
Meet me in front of the hall
in an hour.

207
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:32,257
So... Are you
moving back in?

208
00:11:32,259 --> 00:11:34,993
Till mom and dad
get back, yeah.

209
00:11:34,995 --> 00:11:38,063
Better get used to me
being your legal guardian.

210
00:11:42,902 --> 00:11:44,769
Has carolyn come out
of her room yet?

211
00:11:46,138 --> 00:11:48,139
Nope.

212
00:11:48,141 --> 00:11:50,475
She's still up there...

213
00:11:50,477 --> 00:11:54,145
Sitting next to the corpse
of her dead wife.

214
00:11:56,082 --> 00:11:58,249
You know what I've
been thinking?

215
00:11:58,251 --> 00:11:59,884
What?

216
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:04,923
I've been thinking
it was your idea

217
00:12:04,925 --> 00:12:06,925
To go to the center of the dome.

218
00:12:06,927 --> 00:12:09,060
We never
would've found

219
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:11,463
That egg thing
if you hadn't led us there.

220
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:13,431
She had the
heart attack

221
00:12:13,433 --> 00:12:16,234
Right when we touched it.

222
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:19,037
She died because we touched it.

223
00:12:20,339 --> 00:12:23,908
Bad things happen
when we're together.

224
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:26,077
So, as soon as carolyn's ready,

225
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:29,214
We're just gonna find
somewhere else to stay.

226
00:12:29,216 --> 00:12:32,083
'cause I don't think
I should be around you anymore.

227
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:33,351
Norrie...

228
00:12:33,353 --> 00:12:35,353
I'd like to be alone now.

229
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:39,791
I said I'd like
to be alone.

230
00:12:39,793 --> 00:12:42,861
Leave me
alone, joe!

231
00:12:58,544 --> 00:13:01,146
Carter:
I wonder where ollie went.

232
00:13:01,148 --> 00:13:02,213
Big jim:
Guess he figured
discretion's

233
00:13:02,215 --> 00:13:04,415
The better part of valor.

234
00:13:04,417 --> 00:13:06,351
Just like I thought.

235
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:11,156
Carter,

236
00:13:11,158 --> 00:13:13,158
Secure the well.

237
00:13:23,103 --> 00:13:26,104
Well, now.
That didn't take long.

238
00:13:27,573 --> 00:13:30,074
You're trespassing
on private property.

239
00:13:31,944 --> 00:13:33,978
It's not private anymore.

240
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,313
Ollie:
Well, that's
a peculiar claim,

241
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:37,048
Seeing as the deed's been
in my family

242
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:39,050
For 75 years now.

243
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:41,920
By whose authority
was it rendered un-private?

244
00:13:41,922 --> 00:13:44,222
The township of chester's mill.

245
00:13:44,224 --> 00:13:45,490
Ah.

246
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:48,059
So... Your authority.

247
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:51,196
I'm afraid
I don't recognize that.

248
00:13:51,198 --> 00:13:52,597
Or yours, either, sweetheart,

249
00:13:52,599 --> 00:13:55,500
If you decide to stand
with big jim rennie.

250
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:58,036
In fact, anybody that
stands by big jim

251
00:13:58,038 --> 00:14:00,839
Can look forward to
a tough haul ahead.

252
00:14:00,841 --> 00:14:03,174
See, whatever
food we produce--

253
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:07,111
With my water--
stays with us.

254
00:14:07,113 --> 00:14:09,480
Tell that
to your precious township.

255
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:15,486
Best move away from
that well now, son.

256
00:14:16,622 --> 00:14:18,122
Go on.

257
00:14:18,124 --> 00:14:19,357
Scoot.

258
00:14:21,493 --> 00:14:23,928
wendell.

259
00:14:24,597 --> 00:14:26,097
Kneecap.

260
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:36,474
Linda, put
your gun down.

261
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:39,377
Ollie: Like I said,
this is private property.

262
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:41,646
Any attempt to commandeer
this land,

263
00:14:41,648 --> 00:14:46,417
This well will be met
with most serious consequences.

264
00:14:49,989 --> 00:14:53,191
Now, get off my land.

265
00:14:58,264 --> 00:15:00,064
Junior!

266
00:15:09,675 --> 00:15:11,943
You need any help?

267
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:18,449
How about you take
that gun off your daddy?

268
00:15:47,713 --> 00:15:50,581
Ollie:
I'm asking you
nicely to leave now

269
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:52,583
Before anyone else gets hurt.

270
00:15:52,585 --> 00:15:56,120
♪

271
00:16:19,345 --> 00:16:21,212
You okay?

272
00:16:21,214 --> 00:16:25,283
norrie thinks it's
my fault that alice died.

273
00:16:25,285 --> 00:16:27,552
No. She doesn't
think that.

274
00:16:27,554 --> 00:16:29,253
Come on.

275
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:32,023
I'll let you in
on a little secret.

276
00:16:32,025 --> 00:16:35,226
Women say a lot of things
they don't mean.

277
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:37,028
Especially at that age.

278
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,630
I've never met anyone
like her before.

279
00:16:39,632 --> 00:16:43,401
It's kind of amazing,
to feel that connected.

280
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,636
It's even more
intense at the egg.

281
00:16:45,638 --> 00:16:47,605
The egg?

282
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:51,142
What egg?

283
00:16:52,745 --> 00:16:55,246
Joe, you can trust me.

284
00:16:55,248 --> 00:16:57,548
If it's something
to do with the dome,

285
00:16:57,550 --> 00:17:00,551
We all have a right to know.

286
00:17:02,355 --> 00:17:04,288
Yesterday...

287
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:06,524
Norrie and I, w...

288
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:09,260
We found... This egg.

289
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:13,231
Totally black.

290
00:17:13,233 --> 00:17:16,434
With its own little
dome around it.

291
00:17:16,436 --> 00:17:18,703
Take me to it.

292
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:21,239
Now.

293
00:17:26,678 --> 00:17:29,313
Barbie:
Guess old ollie had
a little more support

294
00:17:29,315 --> 00:17:32,183
Than you anticipated, huh?
Only reason those
farmers are backing him

295
00:17:32,185 --> 00:17:34,318
Is 'cause they need his water
for their crops.

296
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,320
Whoever controls that well
can expect their allegiance.

297
00:17:36,322 --> 00:17:39,424
When we go
back there...
Yeah, hold on, hold on.

298
00:17:39,426 --> 00:17:41,259
When we go back?
That's right.

299
00:17:41,261 --> 00:17:43,161
The three of us
against all those guys?

300
00:17:43,163 --> 00:17:45,063
'cause we just dropped
carter off at the clinic

301
00:17:45,065 --> 00:17:46,464
With his knee shot out,
your son...

302
00:17:46,466 --> 00:17:47,532
We'll muster
extra men, then.

303
00:17:47,534 --> 00:17:48,699
Linda:
Jim, if we do that,

304
00:17:48,701 --> 00:17:50,401
It's only gonna escalate things.

305
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:52,603
There has to be
a diplomatic solution here.

306
00:17:52,605 --> 00:17:55,173
He shot a deputy;
there's no diplomatic solution.

307
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:57,475
We go back there
and we take the well.

308
00:17:57,477 --> 00:17:59,677
Now, I'm gonna go round up
some volunteers.

309
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:01,479
We'll meet at the
diner in an hour,

310
00:18:01,481 --> 00:18:03,081
And we'll move out from there.

311
00:18:04,783 --> 00:18:06,517
All right, hold on.

312
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:08,686
I think I got another way.
Come on.

313
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:12,457
All right, so when jim
showed us this

314
00:18:12,459 --> 00:18:16,094
He mentioned that there were
other artesian wells, right?

315
00:18:16,096 --> 00:18:17,395
So here's ollie's.

316
00:18:17,397 --> 00:18:18,763
Yeah.
What about
these other ones?

317
00:18:18,765 --> 00:18:20,264
You got here, here...

318
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:22,300
Dried out.
Why's that?

319
00:18:22,302 --> 00:18:23,434
Well, back in the day,

320
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:25,236
When ollie's family
first dug their well,

321
00:18:25,238 --> 00:18:26,838
It siphoned off the water
from all the other ones.

322
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:29,240
There also used to be
a small reservoir in town

323
00:18:29,242 --> 00:18:30,775
Before the tower
was built,

324
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:33,311
But ollie's well
sapped that, too.

325
00:18:33,313 --> 00:18:37,148
Okay, so... Say we
destroy ollie's well.

326
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:40,251
And divert the water back to
the dry ones and the reservoir.
That's right.

327
00:18:40,253 --> 00:18:42,453
No more ollie cornering
the market on h2o.

328
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:44,155
We'll need
explosives.

329
00:18:44,157 --> 00:18:45,656
Farmers in town,
they got to have fertilizer.

330
00:18:45,658 --> 00:18:48,392
Well, I know ollie has ammonium
nitrate and blasting caps

331
00:18:48,394 --> 00:18:51,395
At his farm for planting season.
It's dangerous, but...

332
00:18:51,397 --> 00:18:53,798
Yeah, but it's got to be done.
All right, that's what we'll do.

333
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,167
We'll see if we can't get jim
to call an audible.

334
00:18:56,169 --> 00:18:58,536
All right, we got a job to do.

335
00:18:58,538 --> 00:19:00,671
First of all, do we
have enough ammunition?

336
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:03,141
Several people: Yeah. Yes.
Big jim: All right,
second...

337
00:19:03,143 --> 00:19:05,543
Hey, phil. You ever
shot a gun before?

338
00:19:05,545 --> 00:19:08,279
Course I have-- my dad and
my uncles were marines,

339
00:19:08,281 --> 00:19:10,781
So I've been handling
weapons since I was a kid.

340
00:19:10,783 --> 00:19:12,550
I'm counting on each
and every one of you.

341
00:19:12,552 --> 00:19:13,684
Let's do this.

342
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:19,557
Good to see you two.
Just about ready to move out.

343
00:19:19,559 --> 00:19:21,759
Yeah, well, b-before we do
that, I think linda and I

344
00:19:21,761 --> 00:19:23,227
Came up with an alternative.

345
00:19:23,229 --> 00:19:24,529
Barbie's gonna blow up the well.

346
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:27,231
Yeah. We redirect the water
to an alternate source,

347
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,433
It's crisis averted.
What are you, a
demolition expert?

348
00:19:29,435 --> 00:19:31,836
What if you're wrong?
You could contaminate

349
00:19:31,838 --> 00:19:33,504
The town's only
remaining water supply.

350
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:35,640
Then we're worse off
than we were before.

351
00:19:35,642 --> 00:19:38,643
Okay. Your plan goes wrong,
how many people die?

352
00:19:38,645 --> 00:19:39,777
Damn sight fewer

353
00:19:39,779 --> 00:19:41,679
Than if we have
nothing to drink.

354
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:43,381
Now, get this
through your heads.

355
00:19:43,383 --> 00:19:45,516
The only objective
is the well.

356
00:19:45,518 --> 00:19:46,617
The only obstacle
is ollie.

357
00:19:46,619 --> 00:19:48,486
The only way we nip
this in the bud

358
00:19:48,488 --> 00:19:49,820
Is to make an
example of him.

359
00:19:49,822 --> 00:19:51,856
We get ollie, we get the well,

360
00:19:51,858 --> 00:19:54,258
Everyone gets water,
we start growing food again.

361
00:19:57,396 --> 00:20:00,198
Well, I guess he's not
giving us his blessing.
Better hurry.

362
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,333
I'll delay him
as long as I can.

363
00:20:03,802 --> 00:20:07,238
So, tell me, son, want
to put in a application

364
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,207
To be my number two?

365
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:12,843
How about you
don't call me "son"?

366
00:20:12,845 --> 00:20:14,445
That's fair enough.

367
00:20:14,447 --> 00:20:16,581
But make me
understand

368
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:19,217
How you decided to
become a free agent.

369
00:20:22,487 --> 00:20:24,789
My dad kicked me out.

370
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:27,225
Well, fathers and sons--

371
00:20:27,227 --> 00:20:29,527
It's never a walk in the park.

372
00:20:29,529 --> 00:20:30,962
And I can't imagine

373
00:20:30,964 --> 00:20:33,331
Your dad's an easy
man to live with.

374
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:36,234
Especially after
your mother died.

375
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:38,703
He took it hard.

376
00:20:38,705 --> 00:20:40,338
Uh...

377
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:42,740
It was, uh...

378
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:46,010
A tragic accident.

379
00:20:46,012 --> 00:20:49,447
Accident? Is that
what he told you?

380
00:20:49,449 --> 00:20:52,650
My mother died in a car crash.

381
00:20:52,652 --> 00:20:54,919
Oh, that part's true enough,

382
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:57,255
But it wasn't an accident.

383
00:20:57,257 --> 00:20:59,257
It was a suicide,

384
00:20:59,259 --> 00:21:02,393
Pure and simple.

385
00:21:02,395 --> 00:21:04,395
You don't know that.

386
00:21:04,397 --> 00:21:06,397
Oh, but I do.

387
00:21:06,399 --> 00:21:08,532
I'm sure you remember
how troubled she was.

388
00:21:08,534 --> 00:21:11,269
You're lying.

389
00:21:11,271 --> 00:21:13,371
What cause would I have
to lie to you, james?

390
00:21:13,373 --> 00:21:16,374
I'll always tell
you the truth.

391
00:21:16,376 --> 00:21:18,509
Your father, though, uh...

392
00:21:18,511 --> 00:21:20,811
I doubt he ever will.

393
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,283
When this is over,

394
00:21:25,285 --> 00:21:28,019
The town will be well rid
of big jim rennie.

395
00:21:31,723 --> 00:21:33,424
Take it.

396
00:21:34,826 --> 00:21:37,762
It's old as dirt,
but the aim is true.

397
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:42,933
I'll give you a moment.

398
00:21:42,935 --> 00:21:46,737
Sometimes a man needs to be
alone with his thoughts.

399
00:21:52,879 --> 00:21:54,378
Ollie.

400
00:21:56,448 --> 00:21:59,583
Promise me you won't kill him.

401
00:22:04,089 --> 00:22:06,424
'cause I want to do it.

402
00:22:17,736 --> 00:22:20,738
Don't you feel like
the dome's here for a reason?

403
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:22,006
I think it is.

404
00:22:22,008 --> 00:22:23,074
It brought us together.

405
00:22:23,076 --> 00:22:26,344
Me and norrie,
you and barbie.

406
00:22:26,346 --> 00:22:27,712
Me and barbie?

407
00:22:27,714 --> 00:22:30,014
Yeah. Well, aren't you guys,
like, a thing?

408
00:22:32,452 --> 00:22:33,584
Whoa.

409
00:22:46,131 --> 00:22:47,531
It's pink.

410
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:50,101
It was black before.

411
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:30,007
The monarch
will be crowned.

412
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:32,810
What did you just say?

413
00:23:32,812 --> 00:23:34,845
Who are you
talking to?

414
00:23:39,985 --> 00:23:41,952
The monarch will be crowned.

415
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:47,158
What did you just see?

416
00:23:55,534 --> 00:23:57,768
You.

417
00:24:04,976 --> 00:24:07,611
Julia...

418
00:24:07,613 --> 00:24:09,547
What happened
back there?

419
00:24:09,549 --> 00:24:12,116
I don't know.

420
00:24:12,118 --> 00:24:15,519
I think I might be
losing my mind.

421
00:24:15,521 --> 00:24:18,856
What did you mean when
you said you saw me?

422
00:24:18,858 --> 00:24:21,025
Like another me?

423
00:24:21,027 --> 00:24:22,493
Yeah.

424
00:24:22,495 --> 00:24:24,895
And you spoke to me.

425
00:24:24,897 --> 00:24:26,230
I did?

426
00:24:26,232 --> 00:24:28,732
When we saw alice,
she didn't say anything.

427
00:24:28,734 --> 00:24:30,568
When you saw alice?

428
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:32,736
Yeah, yesterday.

429
00:24:32,738 --> 00:24:34,905
When norrie and I touched
the mini-dome.

430
00:24:34,907 --> 00:24:36,974
But that's something
you could have mentioned, joe.

431
00:24:40,913 --> 00:24:43,481
So... What did I say?

432
00:24:43,483 --> 00:24:46,016
I mean, the other me.

433
00:24:48,687 --> 00:24:51,088
"the monarch will be crowned."

434
00:24:51,090 --> 00:24:53,224
The monarch will be crowned?

435
00:24:53,226 --> 00:24:55,793
Yes.

436
00:24:57,229 --> 00:24:59,263
What do you think it means?

437
00:24:59,265 --> 00:25:02,633
I don't know...

438
00:25:02,635 --> 00:25:04,835
But I need
to find out.

439
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:07,505
We saw alice...

440
00:25:07,507 --> 00:25:09,206
And then she died.

441
00:25:09,208 --> 00:25:12,676
Does that mean something bad's
gonna happen to me, too?

442
00:25:40,071 --> 00:25:42,606
♪

443
00:26:07,166 --> 00:26:10,067
Oh, uh... Sorry.

444
00:26:10,069 --> 00:26:12,603
I just needed
to get some fresh clothes.

445
00:26:12,605 --> 00:26:14,338
It's your room.

446
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:16,106
I'm just crashing here.

447
00:26:21,846 --> 00:26:26,016
How'd you end up here
in chester's mill anyway?

448
00:26:26,018 --> 00:26:29,186
I was supposed to go
to this girls' camp...

449
00:26:29,188 --> 00:26:32,156
For reprogramming.

450
00:26:32,158 --> 00:26:34,258
Second horizons. Know it well.

451
00:26:35,895 --> 00:26:40,598
Yeah. Had kind of a preferred
guest membership there

452
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,299
For a stretch.

453
00:26:42,301 --> 00:26:45,202
It was my mom's stupid idea
to force me to go.

454
00:26:47,339 --> 00:26:50,774
If we stayed in los angeles,
she'd still be alive.

455
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:53,344
So it's the bitch's
own fault she's dead.

456
00:26:57,682 --> 00:26:59,116
Anyway...

457
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:01,852
That's how I got stuck here.

458
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:06,824
You ever been to new york?

459
00:27:06,826 --> 00:27:08,292
Lots of times.

460
00:27:08,294 --> 00:27:09,360
You?

461
00:27:09,362 --> 00:27:11,362
Uh-uh.

462
00:27:11,364 --> 00:27:13,797
Who gave you this, then?

463
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:18,769
Someone I used to know.

464
00:27:19,971 --> 00:27:21,639
Whenever
a friend of mine

465
00:27:21,641 --> 00:27:23,073
Would take
a trip someplace,

466
00:27:23,075 --> 00:27:25,209
They'd always bring me back
one of these,

467
00:27:25,211 --> 00:27:28,846
And... Hmm,
it just became a thing.

468
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:32,116
And I promised myself
I would go

469
00:27:32,118 --> 00:27:34,852
To every single one
of these places,

470
00:27:34,854 --> 00:27:36,754
But now...

471
00:27:36,756 --> 00:27:38,188
You're <i>in</i> a snow globe.

472
00:27:39,924 --> 00:27:43,227
I always thought
of chester's mill like a prison.

473
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:47,297
But until recently,

474
00:27:47,299 --> 00:27:49,833
I didn't know what
a prison really was.

475
00:27:52,237 --> 00:27:54,905
You know what'll make me
feel better?

476
00:27:57,809 --> 00:27:58,976
New york city?

477
00:27:58,978 --> 00:28:00,911
I never much liked musicals
anyway.

478
00:28:04,216 --> 00:28:06,684
Oh, that felt good.

479
00:28:06,686 --> 00:28:08,318
Good-bye, paris, France.

480
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:10,254
I got c's in
your lame language anyway,

481
00:28:10,256 --> 00:28:11,722
So you can suck it.

482
00:28:11,724 --> 00:28:14,725
Au revoir,
la bibliotheque.

483
00:28:43,121 --> 00:28:44,955
Los angeles.

484
00:28:55,234 --> 00:28:57,968
It's my fault!

485
00:29:00,004 --> 00:29:02,106
She died because of me!

486
00:29:02,108 --> 00:29:04,475
Oh, my god, no,
no, no, no, no.

487
00:29:04,477 --> 00:29:06,009
I killed her.

488
00:29:06,011 --> 00:29:09,213
No. No, you didn't.
No, you didn't.

489
00:29:09,215 --> 00:29:11,081
No. It's okay,
it's okay.

490
00:29:22,227 --> 00:29:23,527
What'd you see?

491
00:29:23,529 --> 00:29:24,995
Okay, ollie's in the house.

492
00:29:24,997 --> 00:29:26,797
Got a few men up
on the balcony,

493
00:29:26,799 --> 00:29:28,832
A couple more out
by the well.

494
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:32,803
Did you see my... Junior?

495
00:29:32,805 --> 00:29:33,971
No.

496
00:29:33,973 --> 00:29:36,807
All right. Go over
there with that group.

497
00:29:36,809 --> 00:29:39,343
Everybody get ready,
wait for my signal.

498
00:29:39,345 --> 00:29:41,111
Maybe we shouldn't rush this.

499
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,346
We outnumber them.

500
00:29:42,348 --> 00:29:44,114
The longer we wait to attack,

501
00:29:44,116 --> 00:29:45,315
The jumpier
everyone gets.

502
00:29:45,317 --> 00:29:46,884
"attack"?
These are our neighbors.

503
00:29:46,886 --> 00:29:47,885
They're not my neighbors.

504
00:29:47,887 --> 00:29:49,353
Jim, your son is with them.

505
00:29:49,355 --> 00:29:51,421
My son made a choice
to betray me.

506
00:29:51,423 --> 00:29:54,224
Phil, take your group,
go over there by the fence.

507
00:29:54,226 --> 00:29:56,126
Mm-hmm.

508
00:30:06,037 --> 00:30:07,437
Where's barbie?

509
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:10,541
Linda, where is he?

510
00:30:11,476 --> 00:30:12,576
Damn it!

511
00:30:18,516 --> 00:30:20,584
What, he thinks
he's gonna be a hero?

512
00:30:20,586 --> 00:30:22,519
He's gonna jeopardize
my whole plan.

513
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:24,221
All right, we got
to move out now.

514
00:30:24,223 --> 00:30:25,556
My guys stay with me.
Come on.

515
00:30:25,558 --> 00:30:27,558
Let's go. Move out.

516
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:41,939
What do we have here?

517
00:30:41,941 --> 00:30:44,141
Uh-uh.

518
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:51,515
Drop it.

519
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:53,917
Drop it.

520
00:31:21,881 --> 00:31:23,380
Phil!

521
00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:52,943
Man:
That's the well.

522
00:31:52,945 --> 00:31:54,544
They blew up the well.

523
00:31:57,015 --> 00:31:58,382
Fight's over.

524
00:32:00,018 --> 00:32:01,618
Let's get the hell out of here!

525
00:32:01,620 --> 00:32:05,255
Hey! Hey, where you going?!

526
00:32:05,257 --> 00:32:06,356
Stand your ground!

527
00:32:18,202 --> 00:32:21,505
Ollie:
Wasn't enough you blew up
that propane truck, jim.

528
00:32:21,507 --> 00:32:24,107
You had to dynamite
my well, too?

529
00:32:25,343 --> 00:32:27,144
That wasn't me, ollie.

530
00:32:29,514 --> 00:32:31,014
See how he lies?

531
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:37,154
Where you
scurrying off to?

532
00:32:37,156 --> 00:32:40,123
You thought we were
fighting for you?

533
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,133
Fair-weather friends, huh?

534
00:32:54,405 --> 00:32:55,572
What now?

535
00:32:55,574 --> 00:32:58,008
What now?

536
00:33:00,144 --> 00:33:02,379
He's all yours.

537
00:33:02,381 --> 00:33:04,281
Just like you wanted.

538
00:33:23,301 --> 00:33:25,335
Joe, what are you doing?
I could've killed you.

539
00:33:25,337 --> 00:33:26,336
Is he okay?

540
00:33:26,338 --> 00:33:28,038
Phil!
Linda:
He's fine.

541
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,740
Stay out of the road.

542
00:33:35,546 --> 00:33:37,614
Come on.

543
00:33:43,054 --> 00:33:45,022
Junior...
Shut your mouth.

544
00:33:45,024 --> 00:33:47,591
The only thing that's gonna
come out of it is more lies.

545
00:33:49,227 --> 00:33:52,062
You told me she died
in a car crash.

546
00:33:59,137 --> 00:34:01,271
She did die in a car crash.

547
00:34:01,273 --> 00:34:03,440
You told me it was an accident.

548
00:34:03,442 --> 00:34:06,043
But it wasn't
an accident, was it?

549
00:34:06,045 --> 00:34:07,377
Was it?

550
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:12,149
No.

551
00:34:12,151 --> 00:34:14,084
It wasn't an accident.

552
00:34:14,086 --> 00:34:16,153
What happened, then?

553
00:34:16,155 --> 00:34:17,687
Please, junior...

554
00:34:17,689 --> 00:34:19,089
What happened?!

555
00:34:22,593 --> 00:34:26,063
Your mother had been...

556
00:34:26,065 --> 00:34:29,099
Unsteady, for a while.

557
00:34:31,803 --> 00:34:35,739
This one night...

558
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:38,475
We argued, and she ran out.

559
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,812
Got in the car.

560
00:34:44,082 --> 00:34:46,283
A witness said she stopped.

561
00:34:48,553 --> 00:34:51,688
Pointed the lamps
at a 200-year-old oak.

562
00:34:55,159 --> 00:34:58,295
She must've hit the tree
going 80 miles an hour.

563
00:35:00,364 --> 00:35:03,700
Went right through
the windshield.

564
00:35:04,669 --> 00:35:06,870
Duke helped me cover it up.

565
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:12,275
Gave the witness
some cash, and...

566
00:35:12,277 --> 00:35:14,611
The story changed.

567
00:35:20,518 --> 00:35:22,652
Why did you lie to me?

568
00:35:22,654 --> 00:35:23,854
I don't know.

569
00:35:25,523 --> 00:35:28,792
Why did you lie to me?

570
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:33,897
'cause I didn't
want you to know.

571
00:35:33,899 --> 00:35:36,366
I didn't want
you to know...

572
00:35:36,368 --> 00:35:38,435
That...

573
00:35:41,773 --> 00:35:45,208
...That she chose to leave you.

574
00:35:47,378 --> 00:35:50,147
That she chose to leave us.

575
00:35:50,149 --> 00:35:51,381
Ollie:
Enough.

576
00:35:54,652 --> 00:35:57,287
Was that the truth?

577
00:35:57,289 --> 00:35:59,456
I'm sorry, son.

578
00:36:00,725 --> 00:36:02,659
I'm so sorry.

579
00:36:04,262 --> 00:36:06,796
You got a problem with this?

580
00:36:06,798 --> 00:36:08,598
Allow me.

581
00:36:23,781 --> 00:36:25,749
I believe you.

582
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:46,636
Should I tell her
what happened?

583
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:49,739
Later.

584
00:36:49,741 --> 00:36:51,775
Just be her
friend for now.

585
00:36:53,411 --> 00:36:55,345
Go talk to her.

586
00:36:55,347 --> 00:36:57,447
It'll be all right,
I promise.

587
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,821
Joe.

588
00:37:04,823 --> 00:37:07,424
You'll be all right, too.

589
00:37:27,845 --> 00:37:29,679
I'm sorry.

590
00:37:29,681 --> 00:37:32,315
For what I said.

591
00:37:33,918 --> 00:37:35,585
It's okay.

592
00:37:39,657 --> 00:37:42,459
I'm ready to bury my mom.

593
00:37:44,395 --> 00:37:46,296
We waited for you.

594
00:37:46,298 --> 00:37:48,732
Angie said
we should, so...

595
00:37:50,935 --> 00:37:52,936
She's all right.

596
00:37:52,938 --> 00:37:54,404
Your sister.

597
00:37:54,406 --> 00:37:56,339
I know.

598
00:38:15,693 --> 00:38:16,960
Buy you a drink?

599
00:38:16,962 --> 00:38:20,063
People died today, jim.

600
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:23,967
How many?

601
00:38:23,969 --> 00:38:25,535
Three of theirs.

602
00:38:26,504 --> 00:38:28,705
Two of ours.

603
00:38:29,674 --> 00:38:31,941
Because of me,

604
00:38:31,943 --> 00:38:34,511
There is no more
"theirs" and "ours."

605
00:38:34,513 --> 00:38:35,545
Because of you,

606
00:38:35,547 --> 00:38:37,480
Five people died.

607
00:38:37,482 --> 00:38:40,884
Now, they'd be alive right now
if you'd listened to me.

608
00:38:40,886 --> 00:38:43,086
It worked.

609
00:38:43,088 --> 00:38:45,488
Town's got a reservoir again.

610
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:47,624
That's great news.

611
00:38:47,626 --> 00:38:49,592
Yeah, it is.

612
00:38:50,728 --> 00:38:53,863
Not so much for you, though.

613
00:38:53,865 --> 00:38:55,765
Because you wanted
that well, right?

614
00:38:55,767 --> 00:38:58,401
So you could
control it?

615
00:38:58,403 --> 00:39:00,570
Control us?

616
00:39:00,572 --> 00:39:01,805
Isn't that right?

617
00:39:02,873 --> 00:39:05,875
I'm not gonna dignify that
with a response.

618
00:39:05,877 --> 00:39:07,777
You don't need to.

619
00:39:09,714 --> 00:39:12,482
You don't want to make
an enemy of me, barbie.

620
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,920
There's two sides
to that coin, jim.

621
00:39:31,602 --> 00:39:33,670
You're back.

622
00:39:35,639 --> 00:39:37,841
Ollie densmore
is dead.

623
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:40,910
He was gonna
kill my father,

624
00:39:40,912 --> 00:39:42,912
So I killed him.

625
00:39:42,914 --> 00:39:44,881
I thought you joined his team.

626
00:39:44,883 --> 00:39:48,785
Mmm, it was kind of
a trojan horse thing.

627
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:53,623
I went into his camp, and...

628
00:39:53,625 --> 00:39:56,659
Destroyed him from the inside.

629
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:03,166
Why don't you go home, junior?

630
00:40:03,168 --> 00:40:05,735
'cause I don't have a home.

631
00:40:16,180 --> 00:40:19,549
How was your
day, honey?

632
00:40:19,551 --> 00:40:21,985
I've had better.

633
00:40:21,987 --> 00:40:23,720
How about you?

634
00:40:26,824 --> 00:40:29,826
Well...

635
00:40:29,828 --> 00:40:33,463
I've seen some
things today...

636
00:40:33,465 --> 00:40:34,831
That have been
testing the limits

637
00:40:34,833 --> 00:40:36,566
Of my comprehension.

638
00:40:36,568 --> 00:40:38,935
What do you think
of when I say,

639
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:40,770
"the monarch will be crowned"?

640
00:40:43,841 --> 00:40:46,476
What are you talking about?

641
00:40:47,845 --> 00:40:49,712
I wish I knew.

642
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:18,208
♪

643
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:23,146
"the monarch will be crowned."

644
